article.headline: Cent. Arkansas 78, Tenn.-Martin 75
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Marcus Pillow hit a 3-pointer with one second remaining Thursday night to give Central Arkansas a 78-75 win over Tennessee-Martin. Central Arkansas (3-1) led 75-72 with 13 seconds left to play, but Tennessee-Martin's Lester Hudson made a 3-pointer to tie the game at 75-75. Pillow then made his shot to seal the win. Tennessee-Martin (2-2) led 44-29 at the half. But Pillow opened the second half with a jump shot that started Central Arkansas on a 13-2 run that pulled them to within four points at 46-42. Pillow led Central Arkansas with 25 points, Nate Bowie and Durrell Nevels each had 13 and York Sims finished with 10 points. Gerald Robinson led Tennessee-Martin with 19 points, Marquis Weddle had 18, Hudson scored 13, and Olajide Hay contributed 10 points.
